description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a full time Locum Specialty Doctor to work within the Haringey Central Locality Team based at St Ann&#39;s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Central Locality Team provides a locality focused model of care and treatment with improved integration with primary care. The Locality Team structure, with embedded treatment pathways allows the provision of seamless, individualised care. Referrals are received directly into the Locality Teams where they are screened, triaged with senior clinicians and allocated to the most appropriate clinicians to undertake the assessment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Central Locality team works closely with the Haringey Crisis Resolution and Home Treatment Team (CRHTT), which is also based at St Ann’s Hospital and functions as gate-keeper to all inpatient admissions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Strictly no agencies please&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Ruth Kloocke,Consultant Psychiatrist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ruth.kloocke@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
